## Codebase Structure

```
project_root/
├── data/                  # local datasets (large files gitignored)
├── notebooks/             # numbered analytical notebooks
├── output/                # charts (PNG), metadata (JSON), reports (MD/CSV)
├── raw/                   # immutable source materials (papers, downloads, scrapes)
├── wiki/                  # LLM-owned distilled knowledge — index.md, log.md, pages
├── insights/              # evidence-based findings doc + INDEX (project-level)
├── data_sources/          # external API/dataset reference docs (INDEX + per-source)
├── methods/               # operational methodology specs (one folder per method)
├── project_conventions/   # project-bespoke style/process rules (visualization, etc.)
├── deliverables/          # external memos, briefings, decks (per-profile templates)
├── plan/                  # multi-phase implementation plans (gitignored)
├── brainstorms/           # decision-rationale write-ups feeding plans (gitignored)
├── scripts/               # build scripts behind notebooks
├── .claude/
│   ├── conventions/       # full convention protocols (read on demand)
│   ├── hooks/             # Stop nudges (silent unless tripped)
│   ├── skills/            # invokable Anthropic-format skills (slash commands)
│   └── settings.json      # project-shared Claude Code settings
└── CLAUDE.md              # this file
```

## Project Conventions

Project-bespoke style and process rules in `project_conventions/`
— visualization, writing voice, slide design, naming. One file
per domain; `INDEX.md` for quick-nav. Read the relevant file on
demand when work touches the domain. Full protocol:
`.claude/conventions/project-conventions.md` (read on demand).

## Insights Logging

After any substantive data analysis: write `insights/NN_<slug>.md` and update
`insights/INDEX.md`. Full protocol: `.claude/conventions/insights-logging.md`
(read on demand). A Stop hook nudges if artifacts were produced without an
insights doc.

## Wiki

Distilled, queryable project knowledge in `wiki/`, built from immutable
sources in `raw/`. Schema and rules: `wiki/SCHEMA.md`. Use `/wiki-ingest
<raw/path>` to add a source; `/wiki-lint` to audit. Claude owns `wiki/`;
researchers may correct factual errors. See `wiki/README.md` for orientation.

## Script Headers

Every analytical script (R / Python / Stata) starts with a fixed-shape
header comment listing Inputs / Outputs / Seed / Env. Format and examples:
`.claude/conventions/script-header.md` (read on demand). The header is
how `/verify` and future-you trace what produced any given output.

## Analytical Commit Format

Commits that produce or modify analytical artifacts under `output/`,
`insights/`, or `deliverables/<name>/charts/` include `Run:` and `Out:`
lines in the message so `git log -- output/<file>` resolves to a script.
Full protocol: `.claude/conventions/analytical-commit-format.md`
(read on demand).

## Handoff Format

End of any working session that touched a `plan/plan-<name>/`: rewrite
that plan's `handoff.md` in place. Multi-time-scale (within-session,
researcher↔researcher, year-later). Full protocol:
`.claude/conventions/handoff-format.md` (read on demand).

## Plan Structure

Multi-session work lives at `plan/plan-<slug>/{plan.md, handoff.md, log.md}`.
Verification is domain-shaped (sign-of-coefficients, magnitude sanity,
breakpoint alignment), not code-shaped. Full protocol:
`.claude/conventions/plan-structure.md` (read on demand). Cross-link
methodology calls to `decisions/`.

## Decision Records

Methodology calls you'd defend in peer review (deflator choice,
identification strategy, sample restriction): file once at
`decisions/YYYY-MM-DD_<slug>.md`. Format: Decision / Alternatives /
Why-rejected / Key-assumptions / What-would-invalidate. Full protocol:
`.claude/conventions/decision-records.md` (read on demand).

## Methods

Operational, project-internal methodology specs in
`methods/<method-slug>/rule.md` — what we decided to compute and
why, with diagnostic counts that prove the rule is in force. Cross-link
load-bearing changes to `decisions/`. Full protocol:
`.claude/conventions/methods.md` (read on demand).

## Source Registry

Tracked-source watchlist in `sources/registry.yaml` plus dedup ledger
`sources/seen.jsonl`. Use `/scan-sources` to refresh entries due for
re-scrape; `/scan-sources --slug=<slug>` for one source;
`/scan-sources --category=<cat>` to filter; `--force` to bypass the
freq window. Scraped content lands in `raw/sources/<slug>/...md` and
requires explicit `/wiki-ingest` for wiki promotion. Full protocol:
`.claude/conventions/source-registry.md` (read on demand).

## Data Sources

Reference docs for external APIs and datasets in `data_sources/` —
one `<source>_<thing>.md` per source-and-purpose, plus `INDEX.md` for
quick-nav. Each doc carries a `Status: verified <date>` line and at
least one re-fetchable headline anchor. Full protocol:
`.claude/conventions/data-sources.md` (read on demand).

